### Built for Joy: The Curly Waffle S1 "Comfort Menu"

At Curly Waffle, we don't believe in the spec wars.

Most brands give you a spec sheet to impress you (and trap you in "comparison anxiety"). We’re giving you this "menu" to **reassure you.**

We didn't chase the most expensive numbers. We chose the **"right" ingredients.** All of our hardware choices serve one purpose: to power our "zero-tinkering, instant-play" promise.

Here is how the S1 "serves fresh" your pure, unadulterated fun:

| Menu Item | Ingredients (The Specs) | The 'Waffle' Reason (Why It Matters) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Product Model** | Curly Waffle S1 | Your first, and classic, serving of "daily joy." |
| **The Soul (OS)** | **WaffleOS** (Deeply Customized Linux) | **Zero setup. Zero config.** You boot up to a beautiful menu of your games. We spent 1,000 hours tinkering with the OS so you don't have to spend one second tinkering. |
| **The Engine (CPU)** | Performance-Tuned Quad-Core CPU | We don't care about benchmarks. We care that it runs 8-bit to 32-bit classics **perfectly, at full speed, with zero lag.** It's stable, cool, and built to just *work*. |
| **The "Canvas" (Screen)** | 4.0-inch IPS Laminated Display (640x480) | Vibrant, clear, and bright. We insisted on the **perfect 4:3 "retro" aspect ratio** so your *Castlevania* or *Mario* fills the entire screen. No ugly black bars, just pure immersion. |
| **The Feel (Controls)** | High-Precision "Retro-Feel" D-Pad<br>Comfort-Grip Hall Joysticks | The D-Pad was our obsession—it *feels* right. The sticks? Of course, they're comfortable and **will never, ever drift.** Built to last your 100th *Mario* marathon. |
| **The Stamina (Battery)**| 3500 mAh "Comfort" Battery | Provides **6-8 hours of continuous play.** Enough for a long flight or a lazy Sunday afternoon. It's ready when you are. |
| **The "Warmth" (Build)** | "Cream White" / "Caramel Brown"<br>"Warm-Touch" Matte Shell | Forget cold metal and cheap plastic. Holding the S1 feels like holding a **warm mug of coffee.** It's not a cold gadget; it's your personal comfort item. |

